📝 Sum of Second Maximum — Notes
🔹 Problem Restatement

Given a permutation A of size N, compute:

∑𝐿=1𝑁∑𝑅=𝐿+1𝑁
second max of subarray 
[𝐿,𝑅]L=1∑N	​R=L+1∑N
	​

second max of subarray [L,R]
🔹 Key Shift (Critical)

Instead of:

iterate all subarrays ❌

Do:

fix element x → count subarrays where x is second maximum ✅

🔹 When is x second maximum?

A subarray must:

contain x
contain exactly one element > x

👉 That element becomes maximum, x becomes second maximum

🔹 Core Idea

Process elements from largest → smallest

At step x:

all elements > x are already processed
their positions are stored in a set

👉 So we can find nearest greater elements easily

🔹 Data Structure

Maintain a sorted set of positions:

s = positions of elements > x

Initialize:

s = {0, N+1}
🔹 For each element x

Let:

p = position of x

Find:

l2 < l1 < p < r1 < r2

Where:

l1 = nearest greater on left
l2 = second nearest greater on left
r1 = nearest greater on right
r2 = second nearest greater on right
🔹 Counting Subarrays

We want subarrays with:

exactly one greater element

✅ Case 1: Greater element on LEFT (l1)
include l1
exclude l2
include x

Choices:

left boundary: (l2+1 → l1) → (l1 - l2) ways
right boundary: (p → r1-1) → (r1 - p) ways

Total:

(l1 - l2) * (r1 - p)
✅ Case 2: Greater element on RIGHT (r1)
include r1
exclude r2
include x

Choices:

left boundary: (l1+1 → p) → (p - l1) ways
right boundary: (r1 → r2-1) → (r2 - r1) ways

Total:

(p - l1) * (r2 - r1)
🔹 Contribution of x
x * [ (l1 - l2)*(r1 - p) + (p - l1)*(r2 - r1) ]
🔹 Algorithm
Store positions of all values
Initialize set {0, N+1}
Loop x = N → 1:
find p = pos[x]
find l1, l2, r1, r2 using set
compute contribution
insert p into set
print answer
🔹 C++ Code
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int T;
    cin >> T;

    while (T--) {
        int N;
        cin >> N;

        vector<int> A(N + 1), pos(N + 1);

        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            cin >> A[i];
            pos[A[i]] = i;
        }

        set<int> s;
        s.insert(0);
        s.insert(N + 1);

        long long ans = 0;

        for (int x = N; x >= 1; x--) {
            int p = pos[x];

            auto it = s.lower_bound(p);

            int r1 = *it;
            int r2 = (next(it) == s.end() ? N + 1 : *next(it));

            int l1 = *prev(it);
            int l2 = (prev(it) == s.begin() ? 0 : *prev(prev(it)));

            long long left = (long long)(l1 - l2) * (r1 - p);
            long long right = (long long)(p - l1) * (r2 - r1);

            ans += (long long)x * (left + right);

            s.insert(p);
        }

        cout << ans << '\n';
    }

    return 0;
}
🔹 Complexity
Each operation: O(log N)
Total: O(N log N)
🔹 Final Mental Model

Fix x → choose exactly one greater element → count valid subarrays using nearest greater boundaries
